title.narrative: By 2021 the Government will have scaled up access to combination HIV prevention interventions for adolescents and young women.

description.narrative: Through a new partnership with national radio stations and the Tanzania Commission of AIDS, UNICEF facilitated the scale-up of ONGEA radio programme from 4 regions to all 26 regions of mainland. This has increased listenership reach from 9,500 to 4,000,000 adolescents and drastically improved access to correct HIV and SRH information for young women and men. Through UNICEF’s direct support and in partnership with PEPFAR and the Global Fund, 54 districts (31 per cent) were reached with at least three HIV combination interventions for adolescents and young women, an increase from 33 districts in 2020. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/12/2021
